net.imglib2.cache.img

Interface AccessIo<A>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - the access type
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AccessIo.AbstractByteArrayIo, AccessIo.AbstractCharArrayIo, AccessIo.AbstractDoubleArrayIo, AccessIo.AbstractFloatArrayIo, AccessIo.AbstractIntArrayIo, AccessIo.AbstractLongArrayIo, AccessIo.AbstractShortArrayIo, AccessIo.ByteArrayType, AccessIo.CharArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyByteArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyCharArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyDoubleArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyFloatArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyIntArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyLongArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyShortArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyVolatileByteArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyVolatileCharArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyVolatileDoubleArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyVolatileFloatArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyVolatileIntArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyVolatileLongArrayType, AccessIo.DirtyVolatileShortArrayType, AccessIo.DoubleArrayType, AccessIo.FloatArrayType, AccessIo.IntArrayType, AccessIo.LongArrayType, AccessIo.ShortArrayType, AccessIo.VolatileByteArrayType, AccessIo.VolatileCharArrayType, AccessIo.VolatileDoubleArrayType, AccessIo.VolatileFloatArrayType, AccessIo.VolatileIntArrayType, AccessIo.VolatileLongArrayType, AccessIo.VolatileShortArrayType

    public interface AccessIo<A>
    Serialize/deserialize an access to/from a ByteBuffer.

    All implementations for primitive ArrayDataAccess types as well as volatile and dirty variants are implemented as static inner classes.

    Use get(PrimitiveType, Set) to obtain the correct AccessIo implementation for a given PrimitiveType, AccessFlags combination.

    Author:
    Tobias Pietzsch
